name: parsmurf
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "parSMURF" %}
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/AnacletoLAB/{{ name }}/releases/download/v{{ version }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 426013313b22d8fdd0db907e920e869347fb53e9e25cd59f07adc4b2eaf51ad7

build:
  skip: true  # [win]
  number: 0

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - cmake >=2.8
    - make
    - openmpi
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - libgomp      # [linux]
  host:
    - numpy
    - scipy >=1.2.1
    - weave >=0.17.0
    - six >=1.12.0
    - protobuf >=3.7.1
    - openmpi
  run:
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - scipy >=1.2.1
    - weave >=0.17.0
    - six >=1.12.0
    - protobuf >=3.7.1
    - openmpi

test:
  files:
    - parSMURF1
    - parSMURFn
  commands:
    - parSMURF1 --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/AnacletoLAB/parSMURF
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A High Performance Computing imbalance-aware machine learning tool for the genome-wide detection of pathogenic variants.'
  doc_url: https://github.com/AnacletoLAB/parSMURF/blob/master/readme.MD
  dev_url: https://github.com/AnacletoLAB/parSMURF

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - visze
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
